sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Script / Notebook
    participant TH as training-hub SDK
    participant Registry as AlgorithmRegistry
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant GPU as Local GPU(s)<br/>CUDA / torchrun
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>Checkpoints
    participant Tracker as W&B / MLflow<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,Tracker: Flow 1: SFT / OSFT Training

    User->>TH: sft() or osft()<br/>Function call
    TH->>Registry: create_algorithm(algo, backend)
    Registry-->>TH: Algorithm instance
    TH->>HF: Download model + tokenizer<br/>Auth: HF Token (optional)
    HF-->>TH: Model artifacts
    TH->>GPU: Execute training<br/>instructlab-training or mini-trainer
    GPU-->>TH: Training metrics + gradients
    TH->>FS: Save checkpoint
    opt Experiment Tracking Enabled
        TH->>Tracker: Log metrics<br/>Auth: API Key
    end

    Note over User,Tracker: Flow 2: LoRA GRPO Training (ART backend, single-GPU)

    User->>TH: lora_grpo(backend="art")<br/>Function call
    TH->>Registry: create_algorithm("lora_grpo", "art")
    Registry-->>TH: LoRA GRPO + ART backend
    TH->>TH: Spawn ART subprocess<br/>GPU memory isolation
    Note right of TH: ART runs in-process:<br/>vLLM rollout engine +<br/>reward function eval
    TH->>GPU: Single-GPU training<br/>LoRA + rollouts
    GPU-->>TH: Seed LoRA checkpoint<br/>(vLLM V1 workaround)
    TH->>FS: Save LoRA adapter

    Note over User,Tracker: Flow 3: LoRA GRPO Training (verl backend, multi-GPU)

    User->>TH: lora_grpo(backend="verl")<br/>Function call
    TH->>Registry: create_algorithm("lora_grpo", "verl")
    Registry-->>TH: LoRA GRPO + verl backend
    TH->>TH: Generate reward function .py file
    TH->>TH: Convert data to Parquet format
    TH->>TH: Build torchrun CLI command

    par Multi-GPU Distributed Training
        TH->>GPU: FSDP distributed workers<br/>Dynamic/TCP (NCCL)
        TH->>GPU: vLLM rollout workers<br/>Dynamic/TCP (NCCL)
    end

    GPU-->>TH: Stream output + step metrics
    TH->>FS: training_metrics.jsonl
    TH->>FS: Normalized checkpoint<br/>(vLLM adapter compatible)

    Note over User,Tracker: Flow 4: GPU Memory Estimation

    User->>TH: estimate(algorithm, model)<br/>Function call
    TH->>HF: Fetch model config<br/>Auth: HF Token
    HF-->>TH: Model metadata<br/>(params, layers, dims)
    TH->>TH: Calculate VRAM requirements<br/>lower / expected / upper bounds
    TH->>FS: Cache to local CSV
    TH-->>User: Memory estimate result
